{
  "texts": [
    "For calibrated models, this can be achieved via the predicted class scores, although other methods based on dedicated model outputs trained to express the confidence or on density estimation techniques are similarly popular.",
    "Importantly, an algorithm with reliable uncertainty estimates or increased robustness to distribution shift might not always be the best performing in terms of predictive performance 40.",
    "For safe use of classification systems in practice, careful balancing of the trade-off between robustness and reliability over accuracy might be necessary.",
    "So far, Metrics Reloaded focuses on common reference-based methods that compare model outputs to corresponding reference annotations.",
    "We made this design choice due to our hypothesis that reference-based metrics can be chosen in a modality-agnostic and application-agnostic manner using the concept of problem fingerprinting."
  ]
}